Package interfaces

Interface iWalker

  • public interface iWalker
    Interface defining navigation and walking functionalities in a game environment. This interface provides methods for obtaining the player's position, taking steps, and walking along predefined paths within the game.

    • Method Detail

      • setup

        void setup​(java.lang.String customMapfilePath)
        Configures the system to use a custom map file instead of the default worldmap. This method must be called before any operations that require map data are performed to ensure the custom map is loaded and ready for use. If a custom map is not set up using this method, the system will revert to using the default map.
        Parameters:
        customMapfilePath - The relative file path to the custom map file. Path must be relative to your script directory.

      • setup

        void setup​(RegionBox regionBox)
        Configures the system to use a regionbox with the full worldmap. This method must be called before any operations that require map data are performed to ensure the custom map is loaded and ready for use. If a custom map is not set up using this method, the system will revert to using the default map.
        Parameters:
        regionBox - The regionbox you would like to use on the FULL worldmap

      • setup

        void setup​(java.lang.String customMapfilePath,
           RegionBox regionBox)
        Configures the system to use a custom map file instead of the default worldmap with a regionbox defined. This method must be called before any operations that require map data are performed to ensure the custom map is loaded and ready for use. If a custom map is not set up using this method, the system will revert to using the default map.
        Parameters:
        customMapfilePath - The relative file path to the custom map file. Path must be relative to your script directory.
        regionBox - the regionBox you would like the walker to use by default.

      • walkTo

        boolean walkTo​(Tile worldmapTile)
        Attempts to navigate to a specified world map tile. This method calculates the minimap point corresponding to the provided world map tile and performs a tap action to initiate movement towards that location. The method includes a randomization within a randomized small area on the minimap to simulate a more natural movement pattern.
        Parameters:
        worldmapTile - The Tile object representing the destination tile on the world map. This is the target location the player is supposed to navigate to.
        Returns:
        true if the method successfully initiates movement towards the specified location, false otherwise. Note: returning true does not guarantee that the destination will be reached, only that the navigation action was successfully initiated.

      • walkTo

        boolean walkTo​(Tile worldmapTile,
               RegionBox region)
        Attempts to navigate to a specified world map tile within a given region. This method is similar to walkTo(Tile) but takes an additional RegionBox parameter that specifies the region within which the destination tile is located.
        Parameters:
        worldmapTile - The Tile object representing the destination tile on the world map within the specified region.
        region - The RegionBox defining the area within which the destination tile is located. This parameter helps refine the navigation process by providing additional context about the destination's location.
        Returns:
        true if the method successfully initiates movement towards the specified location within the given region, false otherwise. As with walkTo(Tile), success here indicates that the navigation action was initiated, not necessarily that the destination will be reached.

      • walkTo

        boolean walkTo​(Tile worldmapTile,
               RegionBox region,
               java.lang.Runnable actionWhileWalking)
        Attempts to navigate to a specified world map tile within a given region. This method is similar to walkTo(Tile) but takes an additional RegionBox parameter that specifies the region within which the destination tile is located.
        Parameters:
        worldmapTile - The Tile object representing the destination tile on the world map within the specified region.
        region - The RegionBox defining the area within which the destination tile is located. This parameter helps refine the navigation process by providing additional context about the destination's location.
        actionWhileWalking - an action to be performed while walking
        Returns:
        true if the method successfully initiates movement towards the specified location within the given region, false otherwise. As with walkTo(Tile), success here indicates that the navigation action was initiated, not necessarily that the destination will be reached.

      • isReachable

        boolean isReachable​(Tile tile,
                    RegionBox mapRegion)
        Determines if the specified Tile is visible on the minimap. This method checks whether a given tile can be reached based on its visibility on the minimap, implying that it is within a certain range or not obstructed.
        Parameters:
        tile - The Tile to check for reachability.
        mapRegion - The mapregion to get player position from.
        Returns:
        true if the tile is visible and potentially reachable on the minimap; false otherwise.

      • isReachable

        boolean isReachable​(Tile destinationTile)
        Determines if the specified Tile is visible on the minimap, using the already set-up Region from Walker.setup. This method checks whether a given tile can be reached based on its visibility on the minimap, implying that it is within a certain range or not obstructed.
        Parameters:
        destinationTile - The Tile to check for reachability.
        Returns:
        true if the tile is visible and potentially reachable on the minimap; false otherwise.
